sunHwTrapMIB.name: sunHwTrapMIB

revisions.description: Version: 2.3 Add Storage and drive traps
Version: 2.2 Bug fix: missing varbinds in sunHwTrapPowerConsumptionThresholdDeasserted
Version: 1.1 Added keywords for HP SIM integration

sunHwTrapMIB.contactinfo: Oracle Corporation Worldwide Headquarters 500 Oracle Parkway Redwood Shores, CA 94065 U.S.A http://www.oracle.com or contact your local support representative
sunHwTrapMIB.description: Copyright (c) 2007, 2010, Oracle and/or its affiliates. All rights reserved. The SUN-HW-TRAP-MIB describes the hardware related notifications/traps that may be generated by Oracle systems

SunHwTrapThresholdTypeTC.name: SunHwTrapThresholdTypeTC
SunHwTrapThresholdTypeTC.description: Describes whether a threshold is an upper threshold or a lower threshold

SunHwTrapSeverityTC.name: SunHwTrapSeverityTC
SunHwTrapSeverityTC.description: Describes the severity levels that a trap can take.

SunHwTrapHAStateTC.name: SunHwTrapHAStateTC
SunHwTrapHAStateTC.description: Describes the states that a high availability system can take.

SunHwTrapHardDriveStatesTC.name: SunHwTrapHardDriveStatesTC
SunHwTrapHardDriveStatesTC.description: Describes the states a hard drive can be in when hard drive status is reported.

SunHwTrapDisableReasonsTC.name: SunHwTrapDisableReasonsTC
SunHwTrapDisableReasonsTC.description: Describes the reasons that a component is disabled.

SunHwTrapFloatingPointValueTC.name: SunHwTrapFloatingPointValueTC
SunHwTrapFloatingPointValueTC.description: A floating point number converted to a string in decimal notation of the form [-]mmm.dd

SunHwTrapHardDriveProbableCauseTC.name: SunHwTrapHardDriveProbableCauseTC
SunHwTrapHardDriveProbableCauseTC.description: Probable cause for hard drive error

SunHwTrapDriveControllerProbableCauseTC.name: SunHwTrapDriveControllerProbableCauseTC
SunHwTrapDriveControllerProbableCauseTC.description: Probable cause for drive controller error

SunHwTrapStorageVolumeProbableCauseTC.name: SunHwTrapStorageVolumeProbableCauseTC
SunHwTrapStorageVolumeProbableCauseTC.description: Probable cause for storage volume error

SunHwTrapDiagEntityTC.name: SunHwTrapDiagEntityTC
SunHwTrapDiagEntityTC.description: Describes the entity that diagnosed the fault.

SunHwTrapSuspectFruStatusTC.name: SunHwTrapSuspectFruStatusTC
SunHwTrapSuspectFruStatusTC.description: Describes the status of a FRU.

sunHwTrapSystemIdentifier.name: sunHwTrapSystemIdentifier
sunHwTrapSystemIdentifier.description: A text string used to identify the source of the trap. Typically this is the host name.

sunHwTrapComponentName.name: sunHwTrapComponentName
sunHwTrapComponentName.description: The name of the component which is the source of the trap.

sunHwTrapThresholdType.name: sunHwTrapThresholdType
sunHwTrapThresholdType.description: Identifies the threshold type that the sensor is reporting on.

sunHwTrapThresholdValue.name: sunHwTrapThresholdValue
sunHwTrapThresholdValue.description: The threshold setting that has been crossed.

sunHwTrapSensorValue.name: sunHwTrapSensorValue
sunHwTrapSensorValue.description: The threshold sensor's reading at the time the trap was generated.

sunHwTrapSuspectComponentName.name: sunHwTrapSuspectComponentName
sunHwTrapSuspectComponentName.description: Contains the name of a component that is suspected of causing a fault.

sunHwTrapFaultClass.name: sunHwTrapFaultClass
sunHwTrapFaultClass.description: The class represents a hierarchical classification string indicating the type of problem detected, as reported by the fault management subsystem, such as, for instance the Solaris fault manager. Information on the Solaris fault manager can be found at http://www.opensolaris.org/os/community/fm. This object will have a value of NULL if the system doesn't support this information.

sunHwTrapFaultCertainty.name: sunHwTrapFaultCertainty
sunHwTrapFaultCertainty.description: The percentage likelihood that the component is the source of the problem. This object will have a value of 0 if the system doesn't support this information.

sunHwTrapAdditionalInfo.name: sunHwTrapAdditionalInfo
sunHwTrapAdditionalInfo.description: An optional textual description which provides additional information relevant to this notification.

sunHwTrapAssocObjectId.name: sunHwTrapAssocObjectId
sunHwTrapAssocObjectId.description: The object in the entPhysicalTable to which this notification applies. The value is the name of the instance of the first accessible columnar object in the entPhysicalTable conceptual row. If no association exists or the association cannot be determined, this object will have a value of 0.0.

sunHwTrapNewHAState.name: sunHwTrapNewHAState
sunHwTrapNewHAState.description: This object provides the new value of the high availability state after a high availability state change has occurred.

sunHwTrapOldHAState.name: sunHwTrapOldHAState
sunHwTrapOldHAState.description: This object provides the old value of the high availability state after a high availability state change has occurred.

sunHwTrapSeverity.name: sunHwTrapSeverity
sunHwTrapSeverity.description: An indication of the severity of the notfication.

sunHwTrapChassisId.name: sunHwTrapChassisId
sunHwTrapChassisId.description: A text string containing the chassis serial number. When combined with the sunHwTrapProductName, it unambiguously identifies the system. If the source of the trap is a blade, the text string will contain the chassis serial number and the blade serial number, in the following format <chassis-serial-number::blade-serial-number>

sunHwTrapProductName.name: sunHwTrapProductName
sunHwTrapProductName.description: A text string containing the product name. When combined with the sunHwTrapChassisId, it unambiguously identifies the system. If the source of the trap is a blade, the text string will contain the chassis product name and the blade product name, in the following format <chassis-name>::<blade-name>

sunHwTrapHardDriveState.name: sunHwTrapHardDriveState
sunHwTrapHardDriveState.description: The states a hard drive can be in when hard drive status is reported.

sunHwTrapFaultMessageID.name: sunHwTrapFaultMessageID
sunHwTrapFaultMessageID.description: The message ID that can be used to get additional information about the problem from Sun's knowledge article database. This object will have a value of NULL if the system doesn't support this information.

sunHwTrapFaultUUID.name: sunHwTrapFaultUUID
sunHwTrapFaultUUID.description: The universal unique identifier that was assigned to this fault. This object will have a value of NULL if the system doesn't support this information.

sunHwTrapDisableReason.name: sunHwTrapDisableReason
sunHwTrapDisableReason.description: An indication as to why the component was disabled.

sunHwTrapHardDriveProbableCause.name: sunHwTrapHardDriveProbableCause
sunHwTrapHardDriveProbableCause.description: Probable cause for hard drive error

sunHwTrapDriveControllerProbableCause.name: sunHwTrapDriveControllerProbableCause
sunHwTrapDriveControllerProbableCause.description: Probable cause for drive controller error

sunHwTrapStorageVolumeProbableCause.name: sunHwTrapStorageVolumeProbableCause
sunHwTrapStorageVolumeProbableCause.description: Probable cause for storage volume error

sunHwTrapEventTime.name: sunHwTrapEventTime
sunHwTrapEventTime.description: Time stamp for when the fault occurred.

sunHwTrapDiagEntity.name: sunHwTrapDiagEntity
sunHwTrapDiagEntity.description: Name and version of the software component that generated this fault event.

sunHwTrapFaultDescription.name: sunHwTrapFaultDescription
sunHwTrapFaultDescription.description: A textual description of the fault.

sunHwTrapSuspectCnt.name: sunHwTrapSuspectCnt
sunHwTrapSuspectCnt.description: The number of suspected faults diagnosed as the cause of given set of reported hardware errors.

sunHwTrapHostname.name: sunHwTrapHostname
sunHwTrapHostname.description: Hostname of the SP or system

sunHwTrapSuspectFruIndex.name: sunHwTrapSuspectFruIndex
sunHwTrapSuspectFruIndex.description: A sequence number for suspect FRUs.

sunHwTrapSuspectFruFaultCertainty.name: sunHwTrapSuspectFruFaultCertainty
sunHwTrapSuspectFruFaultCertainty.description: The percentage likelihood that the fru is the source of the problem. This object will have a value of 0 if the system doesn't support this information.

sunHwTrapSuspectFruFaultClass.name: sunHwTrapSuspectFruFaultClass
sunHwTrapSuspectFruFaultClass.description: The class represents a hierarchical classification string indicating the type of problem detected, as reported by the fault management subsystem, such as, for instance the Solaris fault manager. Information on the Solaris fault manager can be found at http://www.opensolaris.org/os/community/fm. This object will have a value of NULL if the system doesn't support this information.

sunHwTrapSuspectFruName.name: sunHwTrapSuspectFruName
sunHwTrapSuspectFruName.description: The name of the suspect FRU.

sunHwTrapSuspectFruLocation.name: sunHwTrapSuspectFruLocation
sunHwTrapSuspectFruLocation.description: The location of the suspect FRU.

sunHwTrapSuspectFruChassisId.name: sunHwTrapSuspectFruChassisId
sunHwTrapSuspectFruChassisId.description: A text string containing the chassis serial number. When combined with the sunHwTrapProductName, it unambiguously identifies the system. If the source of the trap is a blade, the text string will contain the chassis serial number and the blade serial number, in the following format <chassis-serial-number::blade-serial-number>

sunHwTrapSuspectFruManufacturer.name: sunHwTrapSuspectFruManufacturer
sunHwTrapSuspectFruManufacturer.description: Name of the manufacturer of this FRU/CRU.

sunHwTrapSuspectFruPn.name: sunHwTrapSuspectFruPn
sunHwTrapSuspectFruPn.description: Number used to order a FRU/CRU (i.e 501-7324-06).

sunHwTrapSuspectFruSn.name: sunHwTrapSuspectFruSn
sunHwTrapSuspectFruSn.description: 18-character FRU serial number for this FRU/CRU (i.e. 1005LCB-0725ZG01JE).

sunHwTrapVoltageFatalThresholdExceeded.name: sunHwTrapVoltageFatalThresholdExceeded
sunHwTrapVoltageFatalThresholdExceeded.description: A voltage sensor has reported that its value has gone above an upper fatal threshold setting or below a lower fatal threshold setting. The sunHwTrapThresholdType object indicates whether the threshold was an upper or lower.

sunHwTrapVoltageFatalThresholdDeasserted.name: sunHwTrapVoltageFatalThresholdDeasserted
sunHwTrapVoltageFatalThresholdDeasserted.description: A voltage sensor has reported that its value has gone below an upper fatal threshold setting or above a lower fatal threshold setting. The sunHwTrapThresholdType object indicates whether the threshold was an upper or lower.

sunHwTrapVoltageCritThresholdExceeded.name: sunHwTrapVoltageCritThresholdExceeded
sunHwTrapVoltageCritThresholdExceeded.description: A voltage sensor has reported that its value has gone above an upper critical threshold setting or below a lower critical threshold setting. The sunHwTrapThresholdType object indicates whether the threshold was an upper or lower.

sunHwTrapVoltageCritThresholdDeasserted.name: sunHwTrapVoltageCritThresholdDeasserted
sunHwTrapVoltageCritThresholdDeasserted.description: A voltage sensor has reported that its value has gone below an upper critical threshold setting or above a lower critical threshold setting. The sunHwTrapThresholdType object indicates whether the threshold was an upper or lower.

sunHwTrapVoltageOk.name: sunHwTrapVoltageOk

The generic 'sensor' trap is generated when the SNMP agent does not recognize the component type. The sunHwTrapThresholdType object indicates whether the threshold was an upper or lower.

sunHwTrapPowerSupplyFault.description: A power supply component is suspected of causing a fault.

sunHwTrapPowerSupplyFaultCleared.description: A power supply component fault has been cleared.
